                     <interp inst="t18290115-175-off928" type="offenceCategory" value="sexual"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-175-off928" type="offenceSubcategory" value="bigamy"></interp>
               bigamy
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>MR. CLARKSON conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290115-175-person1394">
                  OCTAVIUS 
                  YOUNG THISELTON
               <interp inst="t18290115-175-person1394" type="surname" value="YOUNG THISELTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-175-person1394" type="given" value="OCTAVIUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290115-175-person1394" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am parish-clerk of St. Pancras. I produce the register of marriages in that parish, which states that on the 12th of May, 1823, 
               <persName id="t18290115-175-person1395">
                  Daniel 
                  Heath
               <interp inst="t18290115-175-person1395" type="surname" value="Heath"></interp>
